-- Russia Equity Movers: Lukoil, MTS, Novatek, Sistema, TNK-BP
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-05-28T15:26:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-28/russia-equity-movers-lukoil-mts-novatek-sistema-tnk-bp.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose 0.7
percent to 1,290.72 by the close in Moscow. The dollar-
denominated RTS Index gained 0.4 percent to 1,277.15.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH RX) climbed 2 percent to 1,669.30 rubles,
the highest level since May 15.  Russia ’s second-largest oil
company posted a 7.7 percent profit increase in the first
quarter as crude prices rose.  OAO Mobile TeleSystems (MTSS RX) added 4.6 percent to
228.79 rubles, the highest price since May 10. AFK Sistema (AFKS
RX) rose for the third day, gaining 3 percent to 23.492 rubles.
Russia’s biggest mobile-phone operator and its controlling
shareholder were ranked together with the fourth-biggest
weighting in MSCI Inc.’s Russia 10/40 index today, according to
MSCI data. About $550 million may be invested in MTS’s shares
and about $150 million into Sistema’s as a result of the
changes, which come into effect May 31, according to Troika
Dialog.  OAO Novatek (NVTK RX) dropped 0.3 percent to 301.55 rubles.
MSCI Inc. reduced the weighting of Russia’s second-biggest
natural gas producer in its 10/40 index, according to Troika
Dialog.  TNK-BP Holding (TNBP)   added 0.8 percent to 84.70 rubles
after losing as much as 0.8 percent to 83.30 rubles earlier. BP
Plc’s Russian venture said billionaire shareholder  Mikhail
Fridman  resigned as chief executive officer and the company will
be run by a group of executives.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
